#. Tag: command
#, no-c-format
msgid "make clean_ids"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: seg
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Change all IDs to a standard format. This format is <replaceable>Book_Name-"
"title</replaceable>. For example, a section with a title of "
"<computeroutput>First Section</computeroutput> in a book named "
"<computeroutput>Test_Book</computeroutput> will have the following ID after "
"running <command>make clean_ids</command>: <computeroutput>&lt;section id="
"\"Test_Book-First_Section\"&gt;</computeroutput>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Warning: <command>make clean_ids</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To make translation easier, <command>make clean_ids</command> uses the first "
"four characters of the tag as a prefix for the ID. Consequently, you must "
"check out the latest versions of the xml source and translations before "
"running this command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Failing to have the po files checked out before running <command>make "
"clean_ids</command> causes the XML and po files to slip out of sync. And "
"this means all links in the po files have to be manually updated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pre-release software and draft documentation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Completed documentation for pre-release software is not the same thing as "
"draft documentation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Drafts are unfinished versions of a book or article, and their unfinished "
"state is unrelated to the status of the software they document."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In both circumstances, however, it is important to make the status of the "
"software, documentation or both clear to users, developers, readers and "
"reviewers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Denoting pre-release software"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Documentation for pre-release software, especially pre-release software "
"being distributed to testers, customers and partners, should carry a clear "
"mark denoting the beta-status of the software."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "To create that mark do the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add the software&#39;s pre-release version number, or equivalent state "
"information, to the subtitle in your <filename>Book_Info.xml</filename> "
"file. Place this additional text in <sgmltag>&lt;remark&gt;</sgmltag> tags. "
"For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;subtitle&gt;Using Red Hat Enterprise Warp Drive&lt;remark&gt; Version "
"1.1, Beta 2&lt;/remark&gt;&lt;/subtitle&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"add <varname>SHOW_REMARKS</varname> to the <filename>Makefile</filename> and "
"set it to &#39;1&#39;:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#, no-c-format
msgid "SHOW_REMARKS = 1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When your book is built with this text and setting, the software&#39;s "
"status is displayed in clear and unmistakable fashion. PDF builds display "
"the remark on their cover and title pages. HTML builds (both html and html-"
"single) display the remark near the beginning of index.html"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Because this approach makes no changes to the information in "
"<filename>Book_Info.xml</filename> used to generate RPMs, it also ensures "
"there is no ambiguity in the RPM subsystem&#39;s operation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is the writer&#39;s responsibility to remove the <sgmltag>&lt;remark&gt;</"
"sgmltag> tag and its contents and remove or turn off <varname>SHOW_REMARKS</"
"varname> when documentation is updated for use with the release version of "
"the software."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Denoting draft documentation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Unfinished documentation made available to others for review should be "
"labeled clearly as such."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add the draft watermark to your documentation add the <userinput>status="
"\"draft\"</userinput> attribute to the <sgmltag>&lt;article&gt;</sgmltag>, "
"<sgmltag>&lt;book&gt;</sgmltag> or <sgmltag>&lt;set&gt;</sgmltag> tag in "
"your document&#39;s root node. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;book status=\"draft\"&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, your root node is the <sgmltag>&lt;book&gt;</sgmltag> tag in "
"your <filename><replaceable>[book_name]</replaceable>.xml</filename> file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are working on an article or set, the root node is the <sgmltag>&lt;"
"article&gt;</sgmltag> or <sgmltag>&lt;set&gt;</sgmltag> tag in "
"<filename><replaceable>[book_name]</replaceable>.xml</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Adding the <userinput>status=\"draft\"</userinput> attribute causes each "
"page of the document to show the draft watermark. This is by design."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Even if you change only a portion of a work before sending it out for "
"review, marking every page as draft will encourage reviewers to report "
"errors or typos they spot in passing. It will also ensure non-reviewers who "
"encounter the work do not mistake a draft for a finished version."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Denoting draft documentation of pre-release software"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To denote unfinished documentation of pre-release software properly simply "
"do both previously noted procedures."
msgstr ""
